  <data key="d9">"Java class order data bean located in package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities. Uses related classes account data bean, holding data bean, order data bean, quote data bean. Defines methods cancel, equals, get account, get completion date, get holding, get open date, get order fee, get order id, get order status, get order type, get price, get quantity, get quote, get random instance, get symbol, hash code, is buy, is cancelled, is completed, is open, is sell, order data bean, print, set account, set completion date, set holding, set open date, set order fee, set order id, set order status, set order type, set price, set quantity, set quote, set symbol, to html, to string."</data>
  <data key="d10">"The OrderDataBean class is responsible for managing order data, providing access to and modification of its attributes such as order ID, status, type, price, quantity, and completion date. It also offers methods to cancel the order and print its details in HTML format."</data>
