  <data key="d9">"Java class account data bean located in package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities. Uses related classes account data bean, account profile data bean, holding data bean, order data bean. Defines methods account data bean, equals, get account id, get balance, get creation date, get holdings, get last login, get login count, get logout count, get open balance, get orders, get profile, get profile id, get random instance, hash code, login, logout, print, set account id, set balance, set creation date, set holdings, set last login, set login count, set logout count, set open balance, set orders, set profile, set profile id, to html, to string."</data>
  <data key="d10">"The AccountDataBean class is responsible for managing account data, providing access to and modification of attributes such as account ID, balance, creation date, holdings, and login counts. It also offers methods for logging in and out, as well as retrieving related data like orders and profile information."</data>
