<node id="class:com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.TradeServices">
  <data key="d0">"class:com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.TradeServices"</data>
  <data key="d1">"TradeServices"</data>
  <data key="d2">"clase"</data>
  <data key="d3">""</data>
  <data key="d4">{"fan_in": 0, "fan_out": 0}</data>
  <data key="d5">{}</data>
  <data key="d6">[]</data>
  <data key="d7">false</data>
  <data key="d8">null</data>
  <data key="d9">"Java class trade services located in package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader. Uses related classes account data bean, account profile data bean, holding data bean, market summary data bean, order data bean, quote data bean, run stats data bean. Defines methods buy, cancel order, complete order, create quote, get account data, get account profile data, get all quotes, get closed orders, get holding, get holdings, get market summary, get orders, get quote, login, logout, order completed, queue order, register, reset trade, sell, update account profile, update quote price volume."</data>
  <data key="d10">"The TradeServices class is responsible for managing trade operations, providing methods to interact with accounts, quotes, orders, and holdings, allowing users to perform actions such as buying, selling, and canceling orders, as well as retrieving market data and account information. It appears to be a central hub for trade-related functionality, interacting with various data beans to facilitate these operations."</data>
