  <data key="d8">null</data>
  <data key="d9">"Java class trade direct located in package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.direct. Implements interfaces trade services. Uses related classes account data bean, account profile data bean, complete order thread, holding data bean, market summary data bean, order data bean, quote data bean, run stats data bean, trade action. Defines methods buy, cancel order, check dbproduct name, commit, complete order, create holding, create order, create quote, credit account balance, destroy, get account data, get account data from result set, get account profile data, get account profile data from result set, get all quotes, get closed orders, get conn, get conn public, get data source, get holding, get holding data, get holding data from result set, get holdings, get in global txn, get market summary, get order data, get order data from result set, get orders, get quote, get quote data, get quote data from result set, get quote for update, get statement, init, login, logout, order completed, publish quote price change, queue order, recreate dbtables, register, release conn, remove holding, reset trade, roll back, sell, set in global txn, trade direct, update account profile, update holding status, update order holding, update order status, update quote price volume, update quote price volume int."</data>
  <data key="d10">"The TradeDirect class is responsible for managing trade operations, including buying, selling, and canceling orders, as well as maintaining account and holding data. It provides various methods for interacting with a database and managing transactions."</data>
