  <data key="d9">"Java class timer stat located in package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util. Defines methods get avg secs, get count, get max, get max secs, get min, get min secs, get total time, set count, set max, set min, set total time."</data>
  <data key="d10">"The TimerStat class is responsible for managing timer statistics, providing methods to retrieve and update various statistical values such as average, count, maximum, minimum, and total time. It appears to track and store timer-related data for analysis or logging purposes."</data>
