  <data key="d7">false</data>
  <data key="d8">null</data>
  <data key="d9">"Java class trade slsbbean located in package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.ejb3. Implements interfaces trade slsblocal, trade slsbremote. Uses related classes account data bean, account profile data bean, complete order thread, holding data bean, market summary data bean, market summary singleton, order data bean, quote data bean, run stats data bean, trade action. Defines methods buy, cancel order, complete order, create holding, create order, create quote, get account data, get account profile data, get all quotes, get closed orders, get holding, get holdings, get market summary, get orders, get quote, investment return, login, logout, order completed, ping two phase, post construct, publish quote price change, queue order, register, reset trade, sell, trade slsbbean, update account profile, update quote price volume."</data>
  <data key="d10">"The TradeSLSBBean class is responsible for managing trade operations, providing methods for buying, selling, and managing orders, holdings, and account data. It offers various operations for interacting with the trade system, including order creation, cancellation, and completion, as well as retrieving market summaries and quotes."</data>
