  <data key="d8">null</data>
  <data key="d9">"Java class trade action located in package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader. Implements interfaces trade services. Uses related classes account data bean, account profile data bean, holding data bean, market summary data bean, order data bean, quote data bean, run stats data bean, trade direct, trade services. Defines methods buy, cancel order, complete order, create quote, create trade, get account data, get account profile data, get all quotes, get closed orders, get holding, get holdings, get market summary, get market summary internal, get orders, get quote, login, logout, order completed, queue order, register, reset trade, sell, trade action, update account profile, update quote price volume."</data>
  <data key="d10">"The TradeAction class is responsible for managing trade operations, providing methods for buying, selling, and canceling orders, as well as retrieving and updating account and market data. It appears to be a facade or controller class that orchestrates trade-related activities."</data>
