  <data key="d9">"Java class run stats data bean located in package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans. Defines methods get buy order count, get cancelled order count, get deleted order count, get holding count, get new user count, get open order count, get order count, get sell order count, get sum login count, get sum logout count, get trade stock count, get trade user count, run stats data bean, set buy order count, set cancelled order count, set deleted order count, set holding count, set new user count, set open order count, set order count, set sell order count, set sum login count, set sum logout count, set trade stock count, set trade user count, to string."</data>
  <data key="d10">"The RunStatsDataBean class is responsible for managing various statistics related to trading activity, providing getter and setter methods for counts such as buy orders, cancelled orders, holdings, and user interactions. It also offers methods to retrieve and update these statistics."</data>
