  <data key="d9">"Java class trade config located in package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util. Defines methods get access mode, get action trace, get display order alerts, get hostname, get jdbcdriver needs global transation, get long run, get market summary interval, get max holdings, get max quotes, get max users, get next user idfrom deck, get order fee, get order processing mode, get order processing mode names, get page, get percent sent to websocket, get prim iterations, get publish quote price change, get random price change factor, get run time mode, get run time mode names, get scenario action, get scenario count, get scenario mixes, get trace, get update quote prices, get user id, get web interface, get web interface names, increment scenario count, increment sell deficit, next user id, random, rnd address, rnd balance, rnd big decimal, rnd boolean, rnd credit card, rnd email, rnd float, rnd full name, rnd int, rnd new user id, rnd price, rnd quantity, rnd symbol, rnd symbols, rnd user id, set access mode, set action trace, set config param, set display order alerts, set jdbcdriver needs global transation, set long run, set market summary interval, set max holdings, set max quotes, set max users, set order processing mode, set percent sent to websocket, set prim iterations, set publish quote price change, set run time mode, set run time mode names, set scenario count, set trace, set update quote prices, set use remote ejbinterface, set web interface, use remote ejbinterface."</data>
  <data key="d10">"The TradeConfig class is responsible for managing configuration settings for a trade application, providing access to various parameters and modes that control its behavior. It offers a wide range of getter and setter methods for configuring and retrieving settings such as access modes, display orders, and runtime modes."</data>
